:::summary
The four Gospels — Matthew, Mark, Luke, and John — are the four accounts of the life, ministry, death, and resurrection of Jesus Christ that stand at the center of the New Testament and the center of the Christian faith. They are not biographies in the modern sense but theological proclamations: "These are written, that ye might believe that Jesus is the Christ, the Son of God; and that believing ye might have life through his name" (John 20:31). No four documents have shaped human history more profoundly.
:::

